
next
  Framework:
    Changed: codebase split into core (ap_core_*) and ext (ap_ext_*). Other mods can register causes and consequences without modifying core.
    Added: squad ownership registry (register_owner/get_owner). Warfare and BAO excluded automatically.
    Added: automatic save data migrations on version upgrade (orphaned squads released, deprecated keys cleaned)
    Changed: consequence dispatch uses round-robin instead of fixed priority. Equal first-shot distribution across all handlers in a chain.
    Removed: priority field from consequence registration. All consequences in a chain are equal peers.
    Removed: per-consequence chance gates (xmath.chance) and all MCM chance sliders (30 keys). PDA chance sliders remain.
    Removed: RESULT.CHANCE_NEXT from result codes.
    Added: personality system (7 traits, 20 factions including mutants). Derived from GSC design documents. Radiant consequences gated by personality roll (average of relevant traits, 5-95% range). Reactive consequences use hard community tables only.
    Changed: DISPOSITION renamed to PERSONALITY. CATEGORY enum replaced by PERSONALITY field constants. check_disposition removed from all consequence handlers, personality check moved to consumer dispatch.
    Added: mutant faction entries in PERSONALITY table (7 factions: monster, vegetarian, predatory day/night, zombied day/night, special).
    Added: community field to AREA cause payload (was missing, blocked personality gate).
    Removed: job_worship and job_exercise consequences, MCM entries, PDA messages, and item sections.
    Changed: each needs consequence maps to specific personality traits instead of generic discipline gate. Hunger/sleep use survival, money uses greed+perception, jobs use territory/perception, social uses relation.
  Performance:
    Changed: radiant pipeline PACER gate uses os.clock timestamp as first filter, skips all downstream evaluation when interval not elapsed
    Changed: on-map vs off-map detection uses squad.online field (zero luabind)
    Changed: global rate limiting reworked - PACER gate replaces radiant cooldown, sliding window limits per-consequence and globally (MCM configurable)
    Changed: protection gate string allocation guarded behind debug level
    Changed: arrival scan uses cached buffer instead of per-call allocation
  Gameplay:
    Fixed: area_conquest_mutate_smart toggle had no effect on previously conquered smarts
    Fixed: radiant causes dead on first session (deferred init to actor_on_first_update)
    Fixed: PACER retries on protection reject (0.5s instead of burning full interval)
    Fixed: needs scatter init allows negative timestamps for young saves
    Changed: post-arrival wait uses game time (advances during time skips, survives save/load)
    Changed: arrival scan runs every 10s (was 30s), faster squad release
    Added: persistent map markers for elite promote (marks elite's squad until death)
    Changed: map markers transition on squad state: red (active), green (arrived), corpse (dead). Expired markers stay visible 5 minutes before removal.
  Compatibility:
    Fixed: warfare/BAO ownership filters false positive (false ~= nil is true in Lua)
    Changed: is_protected delegates to xsquad.is_protected (shared commander context)
  xlibs (requires xlibs update):
    Added: xsquad.is_protected(squad, opts) composite guard
    Added: xlevel.get_level_id vertex-to-level cache (zero luabind on repeat lookups)
    Changed: is_scripted checks engine fields only (mod-specific fields handled by AP ownership registry)
    Removed: find_online_squads (dead code)

1.2.3
  Core:
    Added: radiant/reactive event split, world-state changes and combat events rate-limited independently (no starvation)
    Added: global radiant cooldown prevents consequence bursts in busy areas (MCM configurable)
    Changed: map marker system decoupled from tracing and optimized for performance
    Changed: consequence chances use pseudo-random distribution for uniform distribution
  Gameplay:
    Fixed: territory changes hands only after the conquering squad physically arrives
    Fixed: stashes only filled when empty, prevents stacking
    Fixed: mutant squads no longer trigger stalker stash events, filtered at cause level
    Fixed: squads no longer churn between nearby locations, with fixed TTL between radiant transitions
    Fixed: revenge only rolls against valid enemy factions 
    Fixed: elite hunters respect the protection list 
    Fixed: stash loot evaluates squad eligibility before chance roll
    Changed: default consequence chances retuned (stash_fill 15%, stash/area/needs 20%, reactive 30%)
  Compatibility:
    Changed: four protection types (permanent, active role, task target, externally scripted) verified through one unified function ensuring single source of truth
    Changed: layered NPC protection: producer rejects radiant squads before any cause evaluates, consequence search excludes all four types, tracker rejects anything that reaches script_squad
    Changed: bounty targets, hostage targets, and externally scripted squads rejected at producer level
  Map & PDA:
    Added: map markers MCM toggle, independent from debug tracing
    Changed: PDA sender rebuilt to match dynamic_news_manager best practices (friendly factions only, online NPC registry)
    Changed: PDA messages come from stalkers already in the world (no server-object lookups, no sender cache)
  MCM:
    Added: version displayed at startup (mod + xlibs)
    Changed: MCM visual refresh
    Fixed: Russian MCM encoding restored (windows-1251)
  X-Ray & xlibs:
    Added: timed events work correctly with demonized_time_events and major modpacks (globals resolve at call time)
    Added: log deadbanding suppresses repeated lines in busy areas for cleaner logs
    Added: consequence rate limit peek without consuming tokens
    Added: cleaner console output (xmath.chance diagnostic noise removed)
    Changed: find_squads distance bounds use inclusive upper
	
1.2.2
  xlibs 1.2.3 dependency.
  Changed: xstash.loot_stash call updated (xlibs rename from loot_stash_to_npc)

1.2.1
  Localization:
    Added: Russian MCM translation

1.2.0
  NPC protection:
    Fixed: named NPCs, traders, quest givers, and guards excluded from AlifePlus
    Fixed: squads already on a mission (Warfare patrols, vanilla scripted routes) are now skipped
    Fixed: guards and bodyguards added to protected list (Rostok, Yantar, Army Warehouses, Jupiter, Pripyat, Sarcophagus, Lab X-18)
    Fixed: Aslan (Dead City barman) ID corrected in protected list
    Fixed: squads no longer respond to their own events
  Gameplay:
    Added: walk/rush toggle per consequence (MCM per-consequence on/off)
    Added: stash protection - NPCs skip stashes containing toolkits and essential items (MCM on/off)
    Added: area conquest mutation toggle - keep squad movement without changing smart terrain ownership (MCM on/off)
    Added: shelter outdoor - squads seek campfires when no indoor shelter nearby (MCM on/off)
    Added: stash fill allowed at bases, ambush and loot still blocked
    Changed: revenge and elite hunters skip friendly factions
    Changed: area conquest only targets enemy or unclaimed territory
    Changed: needs back off after failing to find a destination, other needs get a turn
    Changed: default consequence chances raised to 30% (MCM per-consequence chance sliders)
    Note: needs use game time - thresholds work correctly at any time_factor including real-time
  Smart terrain routing:
    Changed: heal and shelter now target surge shelters, not mutant lairs
    Changed: heal, shelter, social accept any non-hostile location instead of requiring a base
    Changed: guard, worship, exercise send squads to outposts and forward positions, away from bases
    Changed: squads arriving at full locations complete their action then return to simulation
  Stability:
    Fixed: elite kill PDA always showing mutant template instead of stalker
    Fixed: consequence handlers duplicating across save/load cycles
    Fixed: artefact drop/pickup cycling triggering infinite harvest chasers
    Changed: squad tracking uses game time - survives sleep and time acceleration
    Changed: xlibs patch updates no longer require AlifePlus updates
  Internal:
    Changed: debug/trace overhead eliminated below DEBUG log level
    Added: structured arrival logging, smart search diagnostics
    Changed: territory conquest extracted to own module
    Removed: periodic sync (belt and suspenders, never needed), dead enum values

1.2.0-RC1 - "Needs"
  Needs:
    Added: 9 new causes/needs: hunger, sleep, rest, heal, shelter, money, supply, job, social
    Added: 15 new consequences with per-need MCM controls (enable, threshold, chance, action)
    Added: Night gate, faction-aware destination filter, destination limiter
    Added: 8 arrival actions: NPCs consume real inventory items or trade artefacts for supplies
    Added: Needs persisted per-squad in save data
  Event pipeline:
    Added: Radiant/reactive split with independent token buckets
    Added: Consequence token bucket replaces global cause lock
    Added: Radiant exhaustion peek, actor_on_interaction adapter, unscriptable guard
  PDA:
    Added: 168 message variants across 40 categories, stalker/mutant distinction
  MCM:
    Added: Reset button, retuned default chances, cleaned up labels
    Added: Russian translation (Stalker_Boss)
  Performance:
    Changed: MCM snapshot pattern, debug/trace function-swap (zero cost at WARN)
  Docs:
    Added: manifesto.md with GSC vision, engine source proof, developer quotes
  Fixed:
    Fixed: Reactive event starvation (cause lock starving needs and area causes)
    Fixed: wounded_help faction matching (actor_stalker prefix)
    Fixed: PDA messages now distinguish stalkers from mutants
    Fixed: supply_trader exchange giving free items (now requires artefact)

1.1.1
  Fixed: dependency gate uses exact version match instead of string comparison

1.1.0
  10-level elite system replaces binary elite/legend. Alife Ratio balances simulation across maps.
  Elite: 10 levels, AP ammo restock (best k_ap for weapon), engine rank boost (up to 20% accuracy), grenade restock. Alife Ratio: Bresenham ratio gate for on/off-map event distribution, MCM slider (-10 to +10).
  Fixed: elitekill_targeted never firing (bounty was stopping the chain)
  Fixed: PDA message tone, elite buff performance

